title: Irish women open up about abortion before vote
text:
Irish women open up about abortion before vote Wednesday, May 09, 2018 - 01:45
When a 'licence to kill' anti-abortion poster went up outside her house in Dublin, Amy Callahan decided to speak out about travelling to England for an abortion. She's one of many women opening up about their termination experiences before an Irish referendum this month. ▲ Hide Transcript ▶ View Transcript
